🧩 COMPONENTS:

Arduino UNO
Flex Sensors (2) OR Pressure Sensors (FSR) (2)
10k Resistors (2)
Buzzer
Jumper Wires
Breadboard
Foam/Backrest support
USB Cable

🔗 Connections (WRITE THIS IN FILE)
Sensor 1 (Upper Back):
- One end → 5V
- Other end → A0
- 10k resistor from A0 → GND

Sensor 2 (Lower Back):
- One end → 5V
- Other end → A1
- 10k resistor from A1 → GND

Buzzer:
- Positive → Pin 8
- Negative → GND

⚙️ Calibration (IMPORTANT)
1. Upload code
2. Open Serial Monitor
3. Sit straight → note values
4. Slouch → note values
5. Set threshold between both readings

🛠️ Steps to Build (WRITE THIS)
1. Connect both sensors using voltage divider circuit
2. Connect buzzer to pin 8
3. Upload Arduino code
4. Place sensors on upper and lower back area
5. Fix sensors inside foam/backrest
6. Power Arduino using USB
7. Test posture detection

🔁 Working
Sensors continuously monitor back position. When incorrect posture is detected, values drop below threshold and buzzer alerts the user. When posture is correct, buzzer turns OFF.

📈 Future Improvements
Bluetooth alerts
Mobile app integration
Vibration motor instead of buzzer
Data tracking system
AI posture detection
